               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420613-name-993" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-993" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-993" type="surname" value="POLLARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-993" type="given" value="JONATHAN"></interp>JONATHAN POLLARD</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable D</hi> 125.) In consequence of in<lb></lb>formation, I went in search of the prisoner on the 6th of June, and found her walking down Marylebone-lane, about twenty minutes before four o'clock in the afternoon, with this gaiter in her hand, and found this pair of shoes in her apron—I asked where she got them—she said she picked them up—I took her to the station, and she was searched by Eckett—who gave me another pair of shoes—the prisoner was the worse for liquor.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420613-name-994" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-994" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-994" type="surname" value="ECKETT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-994" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>MARY ECKETT</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of William Eckett, a policeman. I live at the station at Marylebone-lane—I asked the prisoner if she had any thing in her pocket—she said she had no pocket, but I found her pocket, and this pair of shoes in it—she said, "For the honour of God, don't produce these shoes; there is plenty besides this against me, keep them for yourself, and say nothing about them."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420613-name-995" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-995" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-995" type="surname" value="WILLIAMS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-995" type="given" value="FRANCIS"></interp>FRANCIS WILLIAMS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am salesman to James Francis Thompson. These shoes are my employer's—they were at a stall outside his shop—I bad seen them safe about half-past one o'clock—I had not missed then till the policeman brought them at half-past six that afternoon.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I met a person; she treated me; she bad these shoes in her basket; she gave them to me, and told me to wait at the corner, which I did, and the policeman and another passed by me; I saw this gaiter on the pavement, and was following a young man, as I thought it might be his.</p>
